old man's beard
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a rampant, troublesome introduced clematis, a strangler of trees and shrubs, whose flowers are replaced in autumn by dense grey-white down.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (cf OLD MAN'S WHISKER(S); TRAVELLERS' JOY) (old man's whisker is also WILD FENNEL)
Citations
Date: 5/3/2002
Source: Independent Herald (Wellington)
Author:
Vol / Page: 17
Edition:
Quote: Old man's beard is a member of the clematis family, and was introduced from Europe as a decorative plant... "This is a good time to look out for old man's beard. It tends to spill out of hedges at this time of year, or you might see it flowering in the tops of trees or along roadsides."
